description: Number of isomorphism classes of connected 3-regular loopless multigraphs of order 2n.
comments: a(n) is also the number of isomorphism classes of connected 3-regular simple graphs of order 2n with possibly loops. - _Nico Van Cleemput_, Jun 04 2014
references: A. T. Balaban, Enumeration of Cyclic Graphs, pp. 63-105 of A. T. Balaban, ed., Chemical Applications of Graph Theory, Ac. Press, 1976; see p. 92.
CRC Handbook of Combinatorial Designs, 1996, p. 651.
links: G. Brinkmann, N. Van Cleemput, T.Pisanski, Generation of various classes of trivalent graphs, Theoretical Computer Science 502, 2013, pp.16-29.
prog: (nauty/bash) for n in {1..10}; do geng -cqD3 $[2*$n] | multig -ur3; done # _Sean A. Irvine_, Sep 24 2015
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
